sub_title: Environmental Engineer - Disaster Risk Reduction & Resilience Specialist at VSO Mozambique
summary: Professional with 4 year  experience in National and International organizations, having worked as: Post-disaster Resilience Assistant in C4D Project (UNICEF); Social and Environmental Safeguard assistant( FNDS); Project Manager of  “Save Our Future'' project (AKSM); Disaster Risk Reduction and Resilience Specialist (VSO). With experiences on Project management, Assessment and Mapping of erosion and flooding risks areas using ArcGIS; Disaster Risk Reduction cycle management, building of Preparedness and action Plan, Early Warning System management, Nature-Based solutions approach,  management of community development projects, production of monitoring and evaluation guidelines, Preparation of Environmental and Social Management Plan, has excellent skills of MS (Excel, Word, and Power Point). In parallel with excellent command of computer programs: ArcGIS, QGIS, KOBO TOOL BOX and Google Earth for Disaster Management.
